content.description: Sit start with hands on a pair of good edges. From there, pull up to a pair of good edges, then trend slightly left to the lip, and mantle atop the boulder.
content.protection: A pad will work. The landing is very good.
content.location: It climbs the center of Snakeskin's east face.

content.description: Sit start with a high left hand pinch and a right hand diagonal incut edge. From there, work straight up the arete on mini-shelfs and edges to reach an easy mantle.
content.protection: A pad or two will work perfectly. The landing is very good.
content.location:
It climbs the southeast arete of Snakeskin. It shares the same start as

Happy Hooker Tribute

.

content.description: Sit start with a right hand crimp and a high left hand pinch on the arete. From there, pull up to the sloping shelf, traverse left along it until reaching the positive holds, throw a heel up and crank to an edge and the eventual lip, and mantle on top.
content.protection: A pad will work well, the landing is very good.
content.location: It climbs the south face of Snakeskin Stone. It shares the same start as Schwing.
